<dl id="n08093c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08093c">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08093c"> 93(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> w<u>as</u> w<u>ere</u> cons, cha<font color="green">[nge]</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Chapter VIII. Grammar.]</font> <font color="green">[Simplification]</font> <font color="green">[T]</font>he consonant change found in many verbs &hellip; has been abolished altogether except in the single case of <i>was, were</i>. <small> Otto Jespersen, <a name="OJGS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#OJGS"><cite title="source">The Growth and Structure of the English Language</cite></a>, 4th ed. (Jul 1923) 175</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
